# Purpose

Enforce test structure, tooling, and naming conventions for backend unit and integration tests.

# Rules

## Tooling

- Unit tests: Vitest (`vitest.config.mjs`)
- Integration tests: Vitest + Supertest against real Express + MongoDB replica set (`vitest.integration.config.mjs`)
- Vitest globals (`describe`, `it`, `expect`, `beforeEach`, etc.) enabled via `tsconfig.json` `"types": ["vitest/globals"]`

## Unit Tests

- Co-locate test files next to source: `foo.ts` ā†’ `foo.test.ts`
- Test pure logic (utilities, repositories, validation helpers) in isolation.
- DO NOT spin up Express or MongoDB for unit tests.

## Integration Tests

- Location: `backend/test/integration/**/*.test.ts`
- Use the shared harness helpers:

```typescript
import { clearCollections, deleteCronJobs, disconnectMongo, getAgent, initServer } from './harness';
```

- Every `describe` block MUST have this lifecycle:

```typescript
beforeAll(async () => {
    app = await initServer();
    agent = getAgent(app);
});

beforeEach(async () => {
    await deleteCronJobs();
    await clearCollections();
});

afterAll(async () => {
    await deleteCronJobs();
    await clearCollections();
    await disconnectMongo();
});
```

- Tag every `it` with requirement IDs: `[AUTH-REG-001]`, `[JOBS-CREATE-001]`, etc.
- Assertions MUST verify the HTTP contract (status code, `body.success`, response shape).
- DO NOT assert on internal handler or module state.
- Use `describe.sequential` when test cases within a `describe` share DB state across `it` blocks.
- Env file: `backend/.env.integration.test` (auto-loaded by `vitest.integration.config.mjs`, overrides shell env).
- Requires Docker MongoDB (`mongo:7`, replica set `rs0`) to be running.

## Required Commands

```bash
cd backend
npm test                  # Unit tests (watch mode)
npm run test:integration  # Integration tests (requires Docker stack)
npm run type-check        # tsc --noEmit
```

# Anti-Patterns

- DO NOT share mutable state between `it` blocks ā€” reset in `beforeEach`.
- DO NOT mock MongoDB or Express in integration tests ā€” use the real stack.
- DO NOT assert on internal module state from integration tests ā€” assert HTTP responses.
- DO NOT omit `clearCollections` + `deleteCronJobs` in `beforeEach`.
- DO NOT use `test.only` or `it.skip` in committed code.

# Checklist

- [ ] Integration tests use `harness` helpers (`initServer`, `getAgent`, `clearCollections`, etc.)
- [ ] `beforeEach` clears collections and cron jobs
- [ ] Every `it` name includes a requirement ID
- [ ] Assertions target HTTP contract, not internal state
- [ ] No `test.only` or `it.skip` in committed tests
